    <h1 class="article-title">Study reveals health potential of chocolate</h1>

    <div id="article-essentials">
        <div class="user-profile">
            <div class="clearfix article-author-box"><div class="user-image"><a href="/home/coraline/Documents/Corpus/readability/corpus/en/html/20120117_www.heraldscotland.com_998648fa54f1a5e658f33d51eaa231745078400669f2affaa69b117e"><img src="/sites/default/files/Marisa Duffy-wee.jpg"/></a></div><p class="user-job">Senior Features Writer</p></div>        </div>
    </div>

            <p class="deck"/>
    
    <div id="article-abstract">
        <p>IT'S what chocoholics have claimed all along.</p>
    </div>

    

    <div class="body-content">
                    <p id="videoHolder"/>
        
        <div id="article-content" property="dc:description">
            
<p>Chocolate, according to new research published today, can be good for you. </p><p>Chocolate and cocoa have been found to reduce the risk of heart disease in women with type 2 diabetes, claims a study by the University of East Anglia (UEA).</p>        </div>
